1
00:00:00,344 --> 00:00:01,144
"While You Were Sleeping"

2
00:00:37,601 --> 00:00:41,274
There are moments in your
life that you're terrified to face.

3
00:00:43,203 --> 00:00:44,449
-Jaechan!
-He's my brother!

4
00:00:46,601 --> 00:00:48,901
And the moment before
you face that terrifying moment...

5
00:00:49,904 --> 00:00:53,369
...there are trivial decisions that you
made which created that moment.

6
00:00:53,876 --> 00:00:57,190
Yes. I'm Mr. Park Junmo's
daughter Park Soyun.

7
00:00:58,203 --> 00:01:01,396
I was wondering what's going
to happen with my dad's case.

8
00:01:01,481 --> 00:01:03,909
We've received documents saying
that she's not pressing charges.

9
00:01:03,994 --> 00:01:06,268
So I don't think
he's going to be indicted.

10
00:01:09,007 --> 00:01:11,536
Yes. I understand.

11
00:01:21,782 --> 00:01:24,785
"Episode 3"

12
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:29,522
And those trivial decisions
will return to us...

13
00:01:30,048 --> 00:01:33,267
...as regrets one day.

14
00:01:35,667 --> 00:01:39,001
If we can change those
trivial decisions we made...

15
00:01:40,084 --> 00:01:43,474
Wouldn't we be able to stop that
terrifying moments from happening?

16
00:01:48,272 --> 00:01:49,409
Seungwon.

17
00:01:50,048 --> 00:01:52,169
Let's go.
I'll take you home.

18
00:01:52,901 --> 00:01:53,835
Let me go.

19
00:01:54,029 --> 00:01:55,353
Pretend you didn't see me and just leave.

20
00:01:55,438 --> 00:01:58,518
Why don't you go to report to the
police or the Prosecutors' office with me?

21
00:01:58,707 --> 00:01:59,578
There must be a way.

22
00:01:59,663 --> 00:02:01,071
No, there isn't any.

23
00:02:01,744 --> 00:02:04,464
I heard the prosecutor had already
dropped the charge.

24
00:02:04,868 --> 00:02:06,987
They made a very quick decision,
which was unfortunately wrong.

25
00:02:07,072 --> 00:02:10,063
Who the heck is that stupid prosecutor?

26
00:02:10,930 --> 00:02:12,232
Who is Seungwon?

27
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,267
He's my brother.

28
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:15,435
What is it?

29
00:02:16,348 --> 00:02:17,570
In my dream...

30
00:02:18,469 --> 00:02:19,943
...the guy named Seungwon...

31
00:02:21,982 --> 00:02:23,610
...killed someone.

32
00:02:25,001 --> 00:02:25,702
Excuse me?

33
00:02:25,934 --> 00:02:28,115
His name is Jung Jaechan?

34
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,206
That's right.
Prosecutor Jung Jaechan.

35
00:02:30,291 --> 00:02:32,801
That prosecutor and the attorney
are in it together with.

36
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:34,467
No way...

37
00:02:34,941 --> 00:02:35,842
What is it?

38
00:02:36,557 --> 00:02:37,542
That prosecutor...

39
00:02:40,907 --> 00:02:41,974
...is my older brother.

40
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:45,363
What?

41
00:02:49,569 --> 00:02:50,937
"Jaechan"

42
00:02:55,868 --> 00:02:56,836
He isn't answering?

43
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:06,166
Jaechan!

44
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:11,106
Soyun. It's mom.

45
00:03:11,498 --> 00:03:13,496
Why don't you sleep
over at Sunghee's house?

46
00:03:15,701 --> 00:03:19,368
I need to talk to dad about something.

47
00:03:19,801 --> 00:03:21,834
Why can't I come home?

48
00:03:22,934 --> 00:03:24,472
Mom. Mom.

49
00:03:28,534 --> 00:03:29,346
Soyun!

50
00:03:31,724 --> 00:03:32,757
Please...

51
00:03:33,368 --> 00:03:34,435
Seungwon.

52
00:03:35,186 --> 00:03:36,653
Come to your senses.

53
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:40,634
You said you had a dream too, right?

54
00:03:40,868 --> 00:03:42,402
Compare it with my dream.

55
00:03:42,734 --> 00:03:43,801
When was the dream about?

56
00:03:43,901 --> 00:03:44,703
It's tonight.

57
00:03:44,788 --> 00:03:46,535
We're wearing the same clothes
from my dream. You and I both...

58
00:03:46,634 --> 00:03:48,168
Then we don't have much time.

59
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:49,734
Tell me about the dream in detail.

60
00:03:51,434 --> 00:03:53,400
It looked like the living room
of a rich house.

61
00:03:54,001 --> 00:03:55,501
But there was a piano in the middle.

62
00:03:56,227 --> 00:03:57,060
Piano?

63
00:03:58,202 --> 00:04:00,910
Yes. A married couple was fighting there.

64
00:04:00,995 --> 00:04:02,774
No. They weren't fighting.

65
00:04:02,859 --> 00:04:05,268
It felt like the wife
was getting beaten up.

66
00:04:07,614 --> 00:04:10,767
At that moment, the couple's
daughter and Seungwon came in.

67
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,167
Please stop, Sir.

68
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,898
Who are you, jerk!

69
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,791
Seungwon, watch out!

70
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:29,669
Seungwon was trying
to stop them from fighting.

71
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:40,280
So, he pushed the husband
and he fell out of the window.

72
00:05:06,827 --> 00:05:08,540
This is all your fault.

73
00:05:09,623 --> 00:05:12,335
I became a murderer because of you.

74
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:14,347
That's how he resented you.

75
00:05:14,501 --> 00:05:17,183
He said that he became
a murderer because of you.

76
00:05:19,868 --> 00:05:21,588
But why is it your fault?

77
00:05:25,236 --> 00:05:26,192
No way...

78
00:05:27,259 --> 00:05:28,439
Is this about Park Junmo's case?

79
00:05:29,434 --> 00:05:30,603
Park Junmo's case?

80
00:05:32,334 --> 00:05:33,759
My friend is having
a piano concert today.

81
00:05:33,844 --> 00:05:34,655
Do you want to go?

82
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,668
You know the piano prodigy
Park Soyun, don't you?

83
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:37,401
It's her father.

84
00:05:37,501 --> 00:05:38,557
The name is Park Junmo.

85
00:05:38,642 --> 00:05:42,035
The victim stated that she
didn't want to press charges.

86
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,889
Therefore, he will not be indicted.

87
00:05:44,974 --> 00:05:45,667
The end.

88
00:05:45,734 --> 00:05:47,571
Wow. It didn't even take five minutes.

89
00:05:50,772 --> 00:05:52,885
That's why he said it's my fault.

90
00:05:52,970 --> 00:05:54,369
Because I let Park Junmo go.

91
00:05:55,959 --> 00:05:59,192
Do you remember where
the apartment in your dream was?

92
00:06:07,650 --> 00:06:10,403
I saw two moons outside
the apartment window.

93
00:06:21,797 --> 00:06:22,515
"Kyomun Securities"

94
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:26,086
"Starland Exhibition"

95
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,602
Hey. Wootak.

96
00:06:41,701 --> 00:06:42,768
Do you want to switch?

97
00:06:43,934 --> 00:06:44,865
You brat.

98
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:46,873
I don't know what he does every night.

99
00:06:50,934 --> 00:06:53,108
Who the heck did this?

100
00:06:53,193 --> 00:06:55,568
A student killed this guy while he
was trying to stop the fight.

101
00:06:55,667 --> 00:06:57,434
He's coming out.

102
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,865
That's terrible.

103
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:00,268
He's still so young.

104
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:02,322
He looks like a good kid.

105
00:07:06,534 --> 00:07:10,997
I was just trying to save
my friend's mother.

106
00:07:14,107 --> 00:07:15,801
Seungwon!

107
00:07:15,901 --> 00:07:17,034
Jaechan. Save me.

108
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:18,266
Jaechan. I didn't do it.

109
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:20,406
Wait.

110
00:07:22,686 --> 00:07:23,627
He's my brother.

111
00:07:23,712 --> 00:07:25,157
I said he's my brother.

112
00:07:25,242 --> 00:07:26,477
Let me go!

113
00:07:33,359 --> 00:07:34,237
Are you awake?

114
00:07:34,534 --> 00:07:35,449
I wasn't sleeping.

115
00:07:35,534 --> 00:07:36,901
Wipe your drool.

116
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,900
Okay.

117
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:41,094
Should we switch, sir?

118
00:07:41,271 --> 00:07:42,118
Yes.

119
00:07:50,627 --> 00:07:51,644
Does your stomach hurt?

120
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:53,868
Is it because of the oyster rice
I had for lunch?

121
00:07:53,934 --> 00:07:55,234
Why is my stomach turning so much?

122
00:07:57,133 --> 00:07:59,212
Then we should go back to the station
so that you can go to the bathroom.

123
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:12,994
What is it?

124
00:08:14,534 --> 00:08:16,095
It's nothing.

125
00:08:16,467 --> 00:08:17,701
Let's go quickly.

126
00:08:29,547 --> 00:08:32,172
You would've killed him
if I didn't stop him.

127
00:08:33,493 --> 00:08:35,316
Seungwon. Seungwon.

128
00:08:38,544 --> 00:08:40,138
Hey. Please step on it.

129
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:43,201
I'm going to soil myself.
Please hurry.

130
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,600
Hey. Turn off the siren.

131
00:08:49,685 --> 00:08:51,235
It's not that bad.

132
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,598
Turn off the siren, you brat.

133
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:02,354
You want me to divorce you and pay
Soyun's tuition for her overseas studies?

134
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:04,752
Do you think I'm UNICEF or Mother Teresa?

135
00:09:05,543 --> 00:09:07,082
You wrote a letter of promise.

136
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:09,868
You said you'll do anything
if I didn't press charges.

137
00:09:10,434 --> 00:09:12,657
You must think that you won something
big just because I wrote you that.

138
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:15,822
The prosecutor and
the law are on my side now.

139
00:09:17,501 --> 00:09:18,781
So why should I do this for you?

140
00:09:25,012 --> 00:09:26,479
Do you know why the law is on my side?

141
00:09:26,989 --> 00:09:28,038
Even if I do this...

142
00:09:40,103 --> 00:09:41,105
Even if I do this!

143
00:09:48,423 --> 00:09:49,772
Even if I do this, no one can touch me.

144
00:09:49,857 --> 00:09:53,001
Why? It's because all of these are mine.

145
00:09:53,067 --> 00:09:54,867
It's because I can do
whatever I want to my things.

146
00:09:54,952 --> 00:09:57,549
The law is fair,
so it knows that very well.

147
00:09:59,579 --> 00:10:01,424
I'll write up the documents again.

148
00:10:48,701 --> 00:10:49,482
Jaechan.

149
00:11:04,898 --> 00:11:10,203
"Secretly, greatly"

150
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,576
What's happening?

151
00:11:17,334 --> 00:11:19,475
Someone set off the alarm.

152
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:20,453
Mom.

153
00:11:20,903 --> 00:11:22,014
Soyun.

154
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,867
Are you okay? Are you okay?

155
00:11:25,968 --> 00:11:27,335
I am okay.

156
00:11:29,434 --> 00:11:31,932
It's so cold.
Just what is going on?

157
00:11:32,017 --> 00:11:34,527
Do you think someone
set off the alarm falsely?

158
00:11:34,701 --> 00:11:35,575
You set off the alarm, didn't you?

159
00:11:35,660 --> 00:11:37,605
I saw you set off the alarm
in the hallway earlier.

160
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:41,215
I thought I saw smoke.

161
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,438
Don't you smell something burning?

162
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:44,337
I don't smell it.

163
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:46,855
Where did you smell
and what did you smell?

164
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:49,535
I think you pulled a prank.

165
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:52,635
Miss. Did you set off the alarm falsely?

166
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:55,536
I saw it.

167
00:11:56,167 --> 00:11:58,548
Was it over there?

168
00:12:00,684 --> 00:12:03,152
I saw the smoke too.

169
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:06,759
So she didn't set off the alarm falsely.

170
00:12:21,868 --> 00:12:22,729
I told you earlier, didn't I?

171
00:12:22,814 --> 00:12:24,501
I told you not to go anywhere
and come straight home.

172
00:12:24,586 --> 00:12:25,645
Why didn't you listen to me?

173
00:12:25,862 --> 00:12:27,381
I had my reasons.

174
00:12:27,466 --> 00:12:29,192
If you hear me out,
you'll know why I did it...

175
00:12:29,277 --> 00:12:31,517
I know that your friend is
Park Junmo's daughter.

176
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:33,434
I know that you came here
because you're worried about her.

177
00:12:33,534 --> 00:12:34,335
You know?

178
00:12:34,434 --> 00:12:35,434
You're acting like this
when you know that?

179
00:12:35,534 --> 00:12:37,080
How can I ignore it when
I'm worried about my friend?

180
00:12:37,165 --> 00:12:38,534
Ignore it!

181
00:12:38,619 --> 00:12:40,440
If you interfere needlessly,
you'll get hurt.

182
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:43,298
Why didn't you answer my call?

183
00:12:43,476 --> 00:12:45,798
I didn't answer it because I was
embarrassed. I was embarrassed of you.

184
00:12:46,934 --> 00:12:47,435
What?

185
00:12:47,534 --> 00:12:48,634
You want me to ignore it?

186
00:12:48,701 --> 00:12:50,942
You're telling me to ignore her when
something bad might happen to my friend.

187
00:12:51,027 --> 00:12:52,020
How can you say that?

188
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:53,001
And you call yourself a prosecutor?

189
00:12:53,097 --> 00:12:54,867
If I didn't stop you,
you would've become a murderer.

190
00:12:54,968 --> 00:12:56,779
You shouldn't be saying that, Jaechan!

191
00:12:57,634 --> 00:12:59,753
"I was wrong. I'm sorry for
being an idiot prosecutor."

192
00:12:59,838 --> 00:13:01,159
That's what you should say.

193
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:05,636
"I'll investigate properly now.
Just trust me and don't worry."

194
00:13:05,721 --> 00:13:07,296
That's what a prosecutor should do.

195
00:13:10,467 --> 00:13:11,525
That's who my brother is.

196
00:13:17,812 --> 00:13:19,098
I guess a prosecutor is not big deal.

197
00:13:19,901 --> 00:13:21,535
You're not a big deal at all.

198
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:26,867
Yes.

199
00:13:27,567 --> 00:13:28,756
I'm not a big deal.

200
00:13:28,841 --> 00:13:31,542
But you're not a big deal either.

201
00:13:32,445 --> 00:13:33,601
I'd get hurt if I interfere
even though I'm a prosecutor.

202
00:13:33,701 --> 00:13:35,135
So what makes you think
that you can interfere?

203
00:13:35,234 --> 00:13:37,035
You're really embarrassing me to the end.

204
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:39,051
Being embarrassed is better
than you getting hurt.

205
00:13:39,849 --> 00:13:41,420
Don't get involved with
Soyun's matters anymore.

206
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:54,333
I want you to sleep over
at Sunghee's house tonight.

207
00:13:54,435 --> 00:13:56,135
It's too late for that.

208
00:13:56,234 --> 00:13:57,615
And what do you think you're going to do?

209
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:59,168
I'm fine.

210
00:14:00,157 --> 00:14:01,758
The two of you should
come to my house for now.

211
00:14:02,397 --> 00:14:03,064
Excuse me?

212
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,388
Who are you?

213
00:14:04,473 --> 00:14:06,012
I'm your friend's
older brother's girlfriend.

214
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,567
We should go before your father sees us.

215
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:08,922
Soyun's Mom!

216
00:14:10,831 --> 00:14:11,917
Soyun.

217
00:14:13,634 --> 00:14:14,854
Soyun's Mom!

218
00:14:16,968 --> 00:14:18,090
Soyun.

219
00:14:22,234 --> 00:14:23,868
There aren't any taxis.

220
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,852
We have a lot of places to go.

221
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:28,859
Really?

222
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,934
Where?

223
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:31,834
Tell me. I'll take you there.

224
00:14:31,963 --> 00:14:32,730
No.

225
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:36,108
I just want you to know that
we have many places to go to.

226
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:44,901
Sir. I had an unbelievable
dream earlier.

227
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:49,901
-In my dream...
-I can't believe the current situation.

228
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,368
Wootak. I have to go to the bathroom.

229
00:14:52,453 --> 00:14:54,436
Yes. We'll go right away.

230
00:14:54,521 --> 00:14:55,568
Please hold it for five minutes.

231
00:14:55,668 --> 00:14:56,433
Five minutes?

232
00:14:56,518 --> 00:14:58,497
No. My sphincter...

233
00:15:00,434 --> 00:15:02,501
I can't even hold it for a minute.

234
00:15:13,813 --> 00:15:15,581
Why are you stopping?

235
00:15:15,802 --> 00:15:16,503
Why?

236
00:15:21,857 --> 00:15:23,387
What is it now?

237
00:15:24,634 --> 00:15:25,568
What's wrong?

238
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:30,234
We have to go home,
but there aren't any buses or taxis.

239
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,101
Where are you headed?

240
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:33,168
I really have to go.

241
00:15:33,253 --> 00:15:34,935
To the bathroom...

242
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:36,282
We're heading to Sanggu-dong.

243
00:15:36,367 --> 00:15:37,101
Please get in.

244
00:15:37,196 --> 00:15:39,238
We're on our way there to patrol.

245
00:15:41,767 --> 00:15:42,863
Thank you.

246
00:16:08,394 --> 00:16:09,557
We met each other before, didn't we?

247
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:10,901
Excuse me?

248
00:16:11,534 --> 00:16:13,773
Don't you remember?
On Valentine's Day.

249
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,109
We almost got into a big accident.

250
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:20,482
That's right.

251
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:23,215
That's why I thought you looked familiar.

252
00:16:26,734 --> 00:16:28,767
It's not that kind of accident.

253
00:16:28,868 --> 00:16:30,623
We're talking about a car accident.

254
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,070
So, you're a policeman.

255
00:16:34,304 --> 00:16:36,868
It was so chaotic back then, so I didn't
even get a chance to apologize to you.

256
00:16:36,968 --> 00:16:38,936
No. That's okay.

257
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:46,534
I'm not fine.

258
00:16:56,067 --> 00:17:00,134
I'm sorry for burdening you.

259
00:17:00,868 --> 00:17:03,689
I heard a little bit about your situation.

260
00:17:04,492 --> 00:17:07,159
What are you doing, Soyun?

261
00:17:08,367 --> 00:17:09,995
Are there only two rooms?

262
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:11,516
Yes. Please sleep in the master bedroom.

263
00:17:11,601 --> 00:17:13,249
I can sleep in Hongjoo's room.

264
00:17:13,334 --> 00:17:14,101
That's okay.

265
00:17:14,186 --> 00:17:16,222
I think it'd be best for us
to sleep in the living room.

266
