Do you have a pimple?

522
00:34:51,834 --> 00:34:53,224
Let's have lunch together.

523
00:34:53,767 --> 00:34:56,127
I'll buy you the sushi
that I promised you.

524
00:34:56,701 --> 00:34:58,714
I'm the prosecutor in
the case you're defending.

525
00:34:58,831 --> 00:35:00,231
You're not the prosecutor now.

526
00:35:00,901 --> 00:35:03,594
You were acting so difficult.
Were you just acting coy?

527
00:35:04,067 --> 00:35:06,508
I saw that you wrapped up
the case by not indicting him.

528
00:35:06,934 --> 00:35:08,139
Who said I wrapped it up?

529
00:35:08,901 --> 00:35:10,535
Mr. Choi told me.

530
00:35:10,624 --> 00:35:11,492
I see.

531
00:35:11,577 --> 00:35:13,286
I haven't reported it
to the superior yet.

532
00:35:13,667 --> 00:35:15,449
When I looked through the documents...

533
00:35:15,534 --> 00:35:17,315
...I realized that
I shouldn't just let him go.

534
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,433
Hey!

535
00:35:21,534 --> 00:35:24,601
It's just an assault case and
the victim isn't pressing charges.

536
00:35:26,734 --> 00:35:28,942
Why are you talking nonsense, Jaechan?

537
00:35:32,734 --> 00:35:34,401
That's when it was just assault.

538
00:35:35,234 --> 00:35:38,234
When I looked at his record,
I began to see some suspicious things.

539
00:35:38,434 --> 00:35:40,501
There are some people
that I have to summon also.

540
00:35:41,767 --> 00:35:43,301
Suspicious things?

541
00:35:43,954 --> 00:35:45,755
People you have to summon?

542
00:35:48,534 --> 00:35:50,081
There are no such things.

543
00:35:50,901 --> 00:35:53,051
You won't find anything no matter how many
times you look through the documents.

544
00:35:53,701 --> 00:35:57,435
So you should know
who you're bluffing to.

545
00:35:57,901 --> 00:35:58,856
Jaechan.

546
00:36:01,100 --> 00:36:02,534
I know what cards you're holding.

547
00:36:11,434 --> 00:36:12,168
Yoobum.

548
00:36:13,100 --> 00:36:15,073
Do you know what's scarier
than not knowing?

549
00:36:20,667 --> 00:36:22,334
Thinking that you know everything.

550
00:36:48,151 --> 00:36:49,888
You must be crazy, Jung Jaechan.

551
00:36:50,075 --> 00:36:52,542
What are you planning
to do by bluffing like that?

552
00:36:53,133 --> 00:36:54,342
Jeez!

553
00:36:55,964 --> 00:36:59,298
45, 15, 35, 43, 27, 33.

554
00:37:00,634 --> 00:37:03,701
45, 15, 35, 43, 27, 33.

555
00:37:07,627 --> 00:37:09,467
Miss Moon Hyangmi.
Just a moment.

556
00:37:10,925 --> 00:37:12,184
You're taking them to get approval
from Senior Prosecutor, right?

557
00:37:12,269 --> 00:37:14,401
Then do I think I'm going
to recycle them right now?

558
00:37:14,501 --> 00:37:15,526
Just a moment.

559
00:37:16,635 --> 00:37:17,839
What are you doing?

560
00:37:18,801 --> 00:37:20,671
I'm going to dig into
Park Junmo's case again.

561
00:37:22,901 --> 00:37:24,040
Here it is.

562
00:37:28,451 --> 00:37:29,682
He's always digging.

563
00:37:29,767 --> 00:37:30,885
He must be a mole.

564
00:37:31,545 --> 00:37:33,212
This is why he can't clear cases quickly.

565
00:37:33,297 --> 00:37:36,783
Working slowly drives you
crazier than being an idiot.

566
00:37:36,868 --> 00:37:38,702
You're going through a lot.

567
00:37:53,015 --> 00:37:55,629
Mr. Choi. Please summon Mr. Park Junmo.

568
00:37:55,714 --> 00:37:58,334
And please set the date for
cross-examination of...

569
00:37:58,434 --> 00:38:00,068
...the doctor from Kiyoung Hospital
and Do Geumseok.

570
00:38:00,167 --> 00:38:02,847
Wasn't that case finished since
we can't issue an indictment?

571
00:38:03,791 --> 00:38:04,973
I brought it back.

572
00:38:06,734 --> 00:38:07,268
And, yes.

573
00:38:07,333 --> 00:38:09,850
Please tell the doctor to bring copies
of the medical history when he comes.

574
00:38:09,935 --> 00:38:10,694
Yes.

575
00:38:12,868 --> 00:38:14,459
I'm going to work overnight again.

576
00:38:14,623 --> 00:38:16,725
I love you, Mr. Choi.

577
00:38:16,810 --> 00:38:20,149
Why are you calling my office
instead of calling my cell phone?

578
00:38:20,234 --> 00:38:22,249
This makes it seem like our
relationship is only official business.

579
00:38:22,334 --> 00:38:24,482
It's because I'm calling
on official business.

580
00:38:24,567 --> 00:38:26,887
Prosecutor Jung would like to summon
Chairman Park Junmo and examine him.

581
00:38:26,972 --> 00:38:28,506
So I wanted to set a date.

582
00:38:31,267 --> 00:38:33,526
Summoning him would be going too far.

583
00:38:33,611 --> 00:38:34,835
Why don't we just go through
documentary examination instead?

584
00:38:34,934 --> 00:38:36,902
It doesn't seem like we can do that.

585
00:38:37,345 --> 00:38:40,068
He looks like he's going to
summon him and issue a warrant.

586
00:38:40,167 --> 00:38:41,534
He's giving me a headache.

587
00:38:42,006 --> 00:38:43,292
That won't do.

588
00:38:43,948 --> 00:38:47,449
I'll try to talk to him so that
he won't give you a headache.

589
00:38:47,534 --> 00:38:48,268
Bye.

590
00:38:48,567 --> 00:38:49,360
Thank you.

591
00:38:51,267 --> 00:38:53,270
Jung Jaechan, that jerk!
He really did it!

592
00:38:57,033 --> 00:38:58,166
Yes, Attorney Lee.

593
00:38:58,481 --> 00:39:01,549
I want you to find out where
Park Junmo's wife and daughter are.

594
00:39:01,634 --> 00:39:02,593
Yes, Sir.

595
00:39:03,241 --> 00:39:06,386
I did inform him of the summons,
but I don't think it will be easy.

596
00:39:06,734 --> 00:39:08,149
I didn't think it will be easy.

597
00:39:08,234 --> 00:39:09,328
Yes. I agree.

598
00:39:10,067 --> 00:39:11,754
Prosecutor Jung.

599
00:39:12,197 --> 00:39:13,948
Chief Park is calling for you.

600
00:39:21,975 --> 00:39:25,054
45, 15, 35, 43, 27, 33.

601
00:39:25,139 --> 00:39:26,516
45...

602
00:39:26,601 --> 00:39:27,810
Jeez.

603
00:39:29,879 --> 00:39:33,126
45, 15, 35, 43, 27, 33.

604
00:39:38,707 --> 00:39:40,144
Come in, Prosecutor Jung.

605
00:39:41,922 --> 00:39:47,610
Thanks to you the average
height of our office went way up.

606
00:39:48,891 --> 00:39:51,061
It will be icing on the cake...

607
00:39:51,146 --> 00:39:53,568
...if you can raise the performance
level of our office.

608
00:39:54,969 --> 00:39:56,090
I'll try my best.

609
00:39:58,990 --> 00:39:59,802
Thanks.

610
00:40:04,247 --> 00:40:08,439
I saw from the reports earlier that
Park Junmo's case was missing.

611
00:40:08,569 --> 00:40:11,115
I heard that it's just an assault and
the victim isn't pressing charges.

612
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:12,315
It's an obvious case.

613
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:14,018
Don't you think you're
holding onto it too long?

614
00:40:15,010 --> 00:40:16,267
There are suspicions that
the medical report was fabricated...

615
00:40:16,352 --> 00:40:18,197
...and there may have been habitual abuse.

616
00:40:20,451 --> 00:40:22,553
You're not doing that because Attorney
Lee Yoobum is defending that case?

617
00:40:27,797 --> 00:40:28,864
No, Sir.

618
00:40:29,874 --> 00:40:33,927
Then you should report it
and focus on other cases.

619
00:40:34,012 --> 00:40:37,727
Aren't you piling up cases and
lowering our performance rate?

620
00:40:39,634 --> 00:40:41,755
I'm going to dig into a little more.

621
00:40:42,910 --> 00:40:44,170
There are more urgent cases.

622
00:40:44,255 --> 00:40:46,601
So why are you so
meticulous about that case?

623
00:40:46,801 --> 00:40:47,834
If you keep working like this...

624
00:40:47,934 --> 00:40:50,535
...it will become a revenge
just like Attorney Lee said.

625
00:40:50,634 --> 00:40:51,682
What's wrong with that?

626
00:40:52,300 --> 00:40:52,817
What?

627
00:40:53,084 --> 00:40:54,037
Whether it's because of revenge or not...

628
00:40:54,122 --> 00:40:56,315
...is it wrong for a prosecutor
to be meticulous about a case?

629
00:40:56,433 --> 00:40:59,322
Are you playing around with my words?

630
00:40:59,407 --> 00:41:01,525
It doesn't matter if you misunderstand
me and think that it's revenge.

631
00:41:01,968 --> 00:41:03,936
If I don't indict him just because I
choose to avoid that misunderstanding...

632
00:41:04,033 --> 00:41:06,467
...it will come back to us
as a more terrifying case.

633
00:41:06,881 --> 00:41:10,268
That's why I'm going to look into
all the previous cases involving him.

634
00:41:10,685 --> 00:41:12,867
Very meticulously.

635
00:41:13,701 --> 00:41:14,801
Hey. You!

636
00:41:18,641 --> 00:41:21,469
Gosh! Chief Park called him "Hey!"

637
00:41:21,822 --> 00:41:22,613
"Hey. You!"

638
00:41:24,751 --> 00:41:29,508
Chief Park wouldn't say
"Hey. You!" that often.

639
00:41:31,734 --> 00:41:36,204
I guess Prosecutor Jung's motto is
to live a short life like fireworks.

640
00:41:36,918 --> 00:41:40,479
He talked back to
Chief Park for every word.

641
00:41:44,300 --> 00:41:45,679
Prosecutor Jung is a hero!

642
00:41:45,764 --> 00:41:48,034
A hero who lives for one day!

643
00:41:50,758 --> 00:41:52,412
I used to get hit when
I acted like that before.

644
00:41:54,925 --> 00:41:57,958
I guess he has to say what he
wants even if he's about to die.

645
00:41:58,231 --> 00:41:59,567
Was he like this in college too?

646
00:42:00,234 --> 00:42:01,284
No.

647
00:42:01,412 --> 00:42:02,946
What does he have
that he's acting so ballsy?

648
00:42:04,427 --> 00:42:05,855
Did he win the lotto or something?

649
00:42:20,770 --> 00:42:21,816
How is the ride?

650
00:42:21,901 --> 00:42:23,402
Isn't it artistic?

651
00:42:23,767 --> 00:42:26,266
This has better mileage
among the luxury vehicles...

652
00:42:26,351 --> 00:42:28,915
...so it will run on the smell of gas.

653
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:30,000
That's technology.

654
00:42:30,067 --> 00:42:31,434
This is our technology.

655
00:42:31,534 --> 00:42:33,357
Would you take a picture of me driving?

656
00:42:33,442 --> 00:42:34,885
Of course.

657
00:42:37,947 --> 00:42:39,159
It's great.

658
00:42:39,244 --> 00:42:42,001
I'm not sure if it's
because it has red interior...

659
00:42:42,100 --> 00:42:44,834
...but you seem like a young CEO.

660
00:42:44,934 --> 00:42:46,244
Young CEO.

661
00:42:47,133 --> 00:42:49,690
If I buy this car,
what should I buy for my second car?

662
00:42:49,844 --> 00:42:50,828
Second car?

663
00:42:52,601 --> 00:42:53,571
My gosh...

664
00:42:55,434 --> 00:42:56,268
That's right.

665
00:42:56,519 --> 00:42:59,966
People buy separate cars for
business and leisure these days.

666
00:43:00,051 --> 00:43:00,790
Of course.

667
00:43:00,875 --> 00:43:02,834
Buying a second car isn't indulgence.

668
00:43:02,934 --> 00:43:03,448
Just a moment.

669
00:43:03,533 --> 00:43:04,600
Yes.

670
00:43:18,774 --> 00:43:19,797
Where are you going?

671
00:43:20,167 --> 00:43:21,182
None of your business.

672
00:43:21,267 --> 00:43:22,034
Why?

673
00:43:22,133 --> 00:43:23,645
I wanted to tell you something.

674
00:43:25,300 --> 00:43:28,371
I yelled at my boss that I'm going
to re-investigate Park Junmo.

675
00:43:28,634 --> 00:43:31,020
I'm going to dig into it no
matter what other people say.

676
00:43:31,105 --> 00:43:32,067
Really?

677
00:43:34,057 --> 00:43:37,360
Why did you give me a hard
time if you were going to do this?

678
00:43:37,445 --> 00:43:39,978
Are your words and
actions always different?

679
00:43:40,101 --> 00:43:40,934
Are you always two-faced?

680
00:43:41,019 --> 00:43:41,501
No.

681
00:43:41,586 --> 00:43:43,068
If you have to say it,
I'm a man of my words.

682
00:43:43,167 --> 00:43:44,580
I don't think so.

683
00:43:45,501 --> 00:43:46,957
By the way, why are you driving that car?

684
00:43:47,534 --> 00:43:48,926
I'm test driving.

685
00:43:50,798 --> 00:43:52,797
Are you going to buy that car?

686
00:43:53,398 --> 00:43:54,465
Maybe...

687
00:43:54,860 --> 00:43:59,759
You're doing this because you believed
my lies about the lotto, are you?

688
00:44:01,192 --> 00:44:03,908
It was a lie?

689
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:07,011
Did you really believe me?

690
00:44:07,989 --> 00:44:08,757
No.

691
00:44:08,842 --> 00:44:11,156
Are you crazy?
Why would I believe such crazy story?

692
00:44:11,246 --> 00:44:12,077
Right?

693
00:44:12,802 --> 00:44:14,285
Thank goodness...

694
00:44:14,741 --> 00:44:17,021
You didn't yell at your boss because
you believed about the lotto, right?

695
00:44:19,133 --> 00:44:20,100
I told you earlier.

696
00:44:20,185 --> 00:44:21,496
I'm not someone who wouldn't
say something I should say...

697
00:44:21,581 --> 00:44:23,669
...or not say something I should
say because of money.

698
00:44:24,948 --> 00:44:27,247
I know that you're not like that.

699
00:44:29,496 --> 00:44:30,343
Then, excuse me.

700
00:44:36,133 --> 00:44:39,747
When I looked through the documents, I
realized that I shouldn't just let him go.

701
00:44:39,832 --> 00:44:40,626
Hey!

702
00:44:40,711 --> 00:44:43,273
That's why I'm going to look into
all the previous cases involving him.

703
00:44:43,358 --> 00:44:44,501
Hey. You!

704
00:44:46,973 --> 00:44:48,407
I must've been crazy.

705
00:44:49,860 --> 00:44:51,682
He's going to buy a second car.

706
00:44:52,162 --> 00:44:53,698
He wants full option too.

707
00:44:54,797 --> 00:44:56,401
Honey. Calm down.

708
00:44:56,486 --> 00:44:58,705
Calm down. It's not a big deal.

709
00:44:59,923 --> 00:45:03,516
Honey. We should upgrade our son,
Kisang's phone while we're at it.

710
00:45:03,601 --> 00:45:06,863
Not a used one, but a new one. Yes.

711
00:45:08,033 --> 00:45:09,366
I'll call you again.

712
00:45:10,334 --> 00:45:11,445
#I'm hanging up.

713
00:45:14,434 --> 00:45:18,315
Sir. I thought about it carefully.

714
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:23,433
If you want to buy a second car,
I think it should be an SUV.

715
00:45:23,518 --> 00:45:26,156
So the model I want to recommend is...

716
00:45:26,559 --> 00:45:27,470
What do you think?

717
00:45:28,734 --> 00:45:30,901
I'll consider it for now.
I'll consider it.

718
00:45:31,783 --> 00:45:32,562
You're right.

719
00:45:32,647 --> 00:45:37,834
I thought it might be too soon
to talk about a second car.

720
00:45:37,934 --> 00:45:39,868
Then when would you
like to buy the main car?

721
00:45:41,434 --> 00:45:43,594
I'm sure I'll buy it someday.

722
00:45:44,334 --> 00:45:45,373
Yes. Someday...

723
00:45:46,878 --> 00:45:48,345
Oh no.

724
00:45:51,667 --> 00:45:53,301
We should go back quickly.
The traffic will be heavy soon.

725
00:45:57,667 --> 00:45:58,416
I knew it.

726
00:45:58,501 --> 00:46:02,369
I knew it when he started to call me
"Heemin" even though I'm his senior.

727
00:46:02,542 --> 00:46:05,864
He was talking back to Chief Park
as if he's ready to leave this field.

728
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:09,333
Hey. That's why...

729
00:46:10,396 --> 00:46:13,119
I know because I had Park
Junmo's case last year.

730
00:46:13,204 --> 00:46:15,667
You can't solve the case
just because you want to.

731
00:46:15,767 --> 00:46:16,967
Oh my goodness.

732
00:46:18,334 --> 00:46:19,417
What are you doing?

733
00:46:19,502 --> 00:46:21,111
What are you doing down there?

734
00:46:22,601 --> 00:46:24,815
I'm planning to leave this field.

735
00:46:31,325 --> 00:46:32,623
Did you hear everything?

736
00:46:33,501 --> 00:46:34,469
Let's talk informally.

737
00:46:34,567 --> 00:46:36,060
You and I are the only ones here.

738
00:46:37,489 --> 00:46:38,315
I understand.

739
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:41,326
I mean. Okay.

740
00:46:43,806 --> 00:46:46,282
Did you not indict Park Junmo
last year, too?

741
00:46:46,367 --> 00:46:47,088
Well...

742
00:46:48,267 --> 00:46:49,168
What happened was...

743
00:46:49,267 --> 00:46:51,800
I'm not trying to pick on you.
I'm asking you because I'm curious.

744
00:46:52,467 --> 00:46:55,079
You're right. I didn't indict him.

745
00:46:55,293 --> 00:46:57,169
No, I did.

746
00:46:58,300 --> 00:47:00,734
If you had indicted him, it wouldn't
have happened again this time.

747
00:47:00,819 --> 00:47:01,701
Don't you regret it?

748
00:47:02,067 --> 00:47:02,853
I don't.

749
00:47:03,187 --> 00:47:05,356
I'm not going to indict him
even if I can do it again.

750
00:47:05,868 --> 00:47:06,435
Why not?

751
00:47:06,723 --> 00:47:07,925
You know that saying?

752
00:47:08,667 --> 00:47:10,761
I will become a caring prosecutor
who defend justice...

753
00:47:11,267 --> 00:47:14,398
...and human rights and care for
the weak and marginalized.

754
00:47:14,868 --> 00:47:16,048
That's the prosecutor's oath.

755
00:47:16,133 --> 00:47:18,748
But there are times that
defending justice...

756
00:47:18,833 --> 00:47:22,172
...and caring for the weak
are in conflict of each other.

757
00:47:22,360 --> 00:47:23,894
Just like Park Junmo's case.

758
00:47:28,565 --> 00:47:30,347
When you indict the husband...

759
00:47:30,770 --> 00:47:33,261
...who earns the living for his family
in domestic violence cases...

760
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:36,220
...the rest of the family will
not have the means to live.

761
00:47:36,854 --> 00:47:41,602
We all know that Park Junmo's wife isn't
pressing charges because she forgave him.

762
00:47:42,159 --> 00:47:46,330
But the reason we're ignoring that
is because we're giving her the choice.

763
00:47:47,431 --> 00:47:49,767
Whether to stay within the thorny fence...

764
00:47:50,201 --> 00:47:53,837
...or to go out to
the middle of thorny bush.

765
00:47:55,539 --> 00:47:57,365
I don't think that we have
the right to tell her...

766
00:47:57,450 --> 00:47:59,915
...to do this or that when we're
living in the flower bed.

767
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:03,113
To indict him and put him in prison
without having that right...

768
00:48:04,667 --> 00:48:05,590
...is not...

769
00:48:06,801 --> 00:48:07,934
...justice.

770
00:48:09,767 --> 00:48:10,680
We're just being brave foolishly.

771
00:48:22,601 --> 00:48:24,249
Someone who can't distinguish
between the two...

772
00:48:24,334 --> 00:48:26,236
...two doesn't have
the right to be a prosecutor.

773
00:48:36,013 --> 00:48:38,767
"Prosecutor Jung Jaechan"

774
00:48:38,983 --> 00:48:41,653
"Seoul Hangang District
Public Prosecutor's Office"

775
00:48:55,167 --> 00:48:56,952
Why are you just laughing?
Why aren't you telling me?

776
00:48:57,167 --> 00:48:59,253
What's higher than ninth level?

777
00:48:59,338 --> 00:49:02,995
It means that you have
to pass the bar exam.

778
00:49:03,947 --> 00:49:05,342
That's nothing. I'll give it a try.

779
00:49:05,661 --> 00:49:07,924
What can I become if I pass the bar exam?

780
00:49:08,009 --> 00:49:11,882
There are many things.

781
00:49:12,033 --> 00:49:13,267
Well...

782
00:49:13,352 --> 00:49:14,481
Welcome.

783
00:49:23,200 --> 00:49:24,636
What is it, Father?

784
00:49:24,721 --> 00:49:26,625
What do you want me to be?

785
00:49:31,601 --> 00:49:35,328
Jaechan. Would you bring me
my cell phone from home?

786
00:49:35,413 --> 00:49:36,858
I forgot it.

787
00:49:36,943 --> 00:49:37,804
Okay.

788
00:49:38,953 --> 00:49:39,986
Jaechan.

789
00:49:43,565 --> 00:49:44,822
What about becoming a prosecutor?

790
00:49:45,300 --> 00:49:46,316
A prosecutor?

791
00:49:46,735 --> 00:49:51,155
Yes.
I would love it if you be a prosecutor.

792
00:49:52,267 --> 00:49:54,801
I'll try it.

793
00:49:55,221 --> 00:49:56,122
I got it.

794
00:49:56,467 --> 00:49:57,227
All the best!

795
00:51:33,262 --> 00:51:34,140
Father!

796
00:51:37,367 --> 00:51:38,443
Father!

797
00:51:43,086 --> 00:51:44,231
No.

798
00:51:44,637 --> 00:51:45,969
Father!

799
00:51:56,767 --> 00:51:57,981
That's when I knew...

800
00:51:58,701 --> 00:52:00,468
...that my father made his decision.

801
00:52:01,502 --> 00:52:06,269
I'm at the funeral of Inspector Jung
Ilsong and bus driver Nam Chuldoo...

802
00:52:06,354 --> 00:52:10,135
...who died while saving the citizens
from the armed runaway soldier.

803
00:52:13,133 --> 00:52:15,966
My father sacrificed himself
to save others and...

804
00:52:16,534 --> 00:52:19,436
...the world called him a hero.

805
00:52:21,505 --> 00:52:25,509
But because of the choice
he made my mother lost her husband...

806
00:52:26,110 --> 00:52:28,078
...and Seungwon and I lost our father.

807
00:52:29,246 --> 00:52:32,716
Rather than being proud
of my father's decision...

808
00:52:32,868 --> 00:52:34,084
...I resented him.

809
00:52:36,654 --> 00:52:39,189
My father's decision
was heroic for people...

810
00:52:40,291 --> 00:52:42,059
...but it was foolish pride to me.

811
00:52:57,367 --> 00:52:58,208
What is it?

812
00:52:58,434 --> 00:53:00,010
Wow. That's amazing.

813
00:53:00,744 --> 00:53:02,412
I was wondering if it would happen.

814
00:53:02,813 --> 00:53:03,547
What are you talking about?

815
00:53:04,882 --> 00:53:06,265
Don't you remember me?

816
00:53:06,350 --> 00:53:08,507
I was almost in a car
accident on Valentine's Day...

817
00:53:09,501 --> 00:53:10,587
Are you alright?

818
00:53:11,868 --> 00:53:12,657
Yes.

819
00:53:14,191 --> 00:53:16,159
Ah, the accident...

820
00:53:17,061 --> 00:53:18,811
I should've thanked you sooner.

821
00:53:18,896 --> 00:53:19,930
I'm Han Wootak.

822
00:53:20,751 --> 00:53:22,899
Yes. I'm Jung Jaechan.

823
00:53:23,601 --> 00:53:24,502
You're a prosecutor.

824
00:53:24,601 --> 00:53:26,364
Yes. I work here.

825
00:53:27,767 --> 00:53:28,799
Were you hurt?

826
00:53:28,884 --> 00:53:30,923
No. I'm fine thanks to you.

827
00:53:31,008 --> 00:53:33,510
I wanted to treat you after that day
and I finally meet you like this.

828
00:53:34,434 --> 00:53:35,846
How about dinner tonight?

829
00:53:36,200 --> 00:53:37,381
Do you have plans?

830
00:53:39,058 --> 00:53:39,918
No. I don't have plans but...

831
00:53:40,003 --> 00:53:41,031
Then let's go.

832
00:53:41,701 --> 00:53:42,953
I'll treat you to barbeque.

833
00:53:43,067 --> 00:53:44,234
Okay.

834
00:53:48,225 --> 00:53:49,326
I was born in the year of dragon.

835
00:53:49,501 --> 00:53:50,761
We're the same age then.

836
00:53:51,261 --> 00:53:52,545
Really?

837
00:53:52,630 --> 00:53:54,249
Then should we just speak
informally to each other?

838
00:53:54,334 --> 00:53:55,298
I don't want to.

839
00:53:58,268 --> 00:54:00,904
"Hongjoo Samgyeopsal"

840
00:54:02,650 --> 00:54:04,550
Hey. You don't need to help.
Just go and study.

841
00:54:04,635 --> 00:54:06,125
I'm not helping you.

842
00:54:06,210 --> 00:54:07,359
It's because I'm bored.

843
00:54:07,444 --> 00:54:09,235
I can stand being bored.

844
00:54:09,334 --> 00:54:11,801
Why do you have so many
things you just can't stand?

845
00:54:11,939 --> 00:54:13,935
Just like someone else,
you're inside and outside...

846
00:54:14,033 --> 00:54:14,788
...are so different from each other.

847
00:54:14,873 --> 00:54:17,268
You act like you're strong,
but you're actually weak.

848
00:54:17,353 --> 00:54:20,202
You seem kind, but you say mean things.

849
00:54:22,234 --> 00:54:24,562
Lady. She plays piano.

850
00:54:24,647 --> 00:54:26,830
You can't let her use hurt her hands.

851
00:54:32,801 --> 00:54:33,435
Lady?

852
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:34,400
Who are you talking to?

853
00:54:34,485 --> 00:54:35,205
Where is she?

854
00:54:38,133 --> 00:54:39,404
This is such a coincidence.

855
00:54:39,667 --> 00:54:40,693
We see each other like this again.

856
00:54:40,778 --> 00:54:41,674
I know, right.

857
00:54:43,077 --> 00:54:45,782
I took her all the way home
in my police car recently.

858
00:54:45,950 --> 00:54:48,952
I was craving pork belly, so I was
trying to find a place and we came here.

859
00:54:49,037 --> 00:54:51,288
This is such a coincidence.

860
00:54:51,580 --> 00:54:54,091
I regretted not asking you for your name.

861
00:54:55,267 --> 00:54:56,293
What's your name?

862
00:54:57,594 --> 00:54:58,963
I'm Nam Hongjoo.

863
00:54:59,048 --> 00:54:59,890
I'm Han Wootak.

864
00:54:59,975 --> 00:55:00,917
I was born in the year of dragon in 1988.

865
00:55:01,002 --> 00:55:03,048
I was born in
the year of dragon in 1988 also.

866
00:55:03,133 --> 00:55:04,818
Then should we just speak
to each other informally?

867
00:55:04,903 --> 00:55:05,701
Fine.

868
00:55:05,801 --> 00:55:08,772
Yes. People who are same age
should speak to each other informally.

869
00:55:10,074 --> 00:55:12,871
Wait a minute. Now that I think
about it, there are three dragons here.

870
00:55:12,956 --> 00:55:15,033
We're like the three flying dragons.

871
00:55:15,133 --> 00:55:16,847
What?
Three flying dragons?

872
00:55:17,311 --> 00:55:18,900
He's so funny.

873
00:55:20,634 --> 00:55:23,987
By the way, you look so
much better without glasses.

874
00:55:24,587 --> 00:55:25,922
Do I really?

875
00:55:28,300 --> 00:55:29,333
Gosh.

876
00:55:33,931 --> 00:55:36,533
I found out where Park Junmo's
wife and daughter are at.

877
00:55:38,602 --> 00:55:39,436
Where are they?

878
00:55:48,078 --> 00:55:50,514
I clearly told you not to get
involved with Soyun, didn't I?

879
00:55:50,676 --> 00:55:51,602
Why are you here?

880
00:55:51,701 --> 00:55:52,948
And why are you wearing that apron?

881
00:55:54,722 --> 00:55:56,356
That's what I want to ask you.

882
00:55:58,115 --> 00:55:59,607
That brat.

883
00:56:00,045 --> 00:56:02,759
I thought the two of you
are affectionate brothers...

884
00:56:03,592 --> 00:56:04,615
...but you guys are just normal.

885
00:56:04,700 --> 00:56:06,435
Did you know that we're brothers too?

886
00:56:09,359 --> 00:56:10,357
This is not coincidence is it?

887
00:56:10,740 --> 00:56:12,553
How we met earlier and
coming to this restaurant also...

888
00:56:12,638 --> 00:56:14,334
I'm curious about that also.

889
00:56:14,724 --> 00:56:16,139
Is this a coincidence...

890
00:56:17,797 --> 00:56:19,176
...or is this fate?

891
00:56:19,288 --> 00:56:21,166
Jeez. What do you think you're doing?

892
00:56:21,901 --> 00:56:24,047
I don't sense anything.
I don't feel anything either.

893
00:56:25,601 --> 00:56:26,583
Is this not fate?

894
00:56:29,302 --> 00:56:30,270
Where are you going?

895
00:56:30,463 --> 00:56:31,655
I'm going to the bathroom.

896
00:56:35,557 --> 00:56:37,194
Is it going to happen just like my dream?

897
00:56:37,868 --> 00:56:38,962
If it's like my dream...

898
00:56:39,736 --> 00:56:43,533
My partner and I were going to a pork
belly place and ran into Jung Jaechan.

899
00:56:44,067 --> 00:56:47,137
In my dream, we just greeted each
other and went our separate ways.

900
00:56:47,538 --> 00:56:49,472
Then my partner and came here.

901
00:56:51,441 --> 00:56:52,709
It's just like my dream.

902
00:56:53,167 --> 00:56:55,011
The customers are wearing
the same clothes...

903
00:56:55,534 --> 00:56:58,215
...and ordered the same thing
as in my dream.

904
00:56:59,767 --> 00:57:03,153
The only thing I changed
was a trivial thing.

905
00:57:04,755 --> 00:57:08,758
I brought that person here
instead of my partner.

906
00:57:13,163 --> 00:57:15,510
Stop joking around and tell me the truth.

907
00:57:15,603 --> 00:57:16,814
Is this all a coincidence?

908
00:57:16,899 --> 00:57:19,202
Or did you plan something
by bringing me here?

909
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:21,634
Answer me without saying this is fate.

910
00:57:21,719 --> 00:57:22,828
Just a moment.

911
00:57:23,185 --> 00:57:25,599
Take two orders of kimchi stew
to table three.

912
00:57:25,834 --> 00:57:27,010
Okay.

913
00:57:29,534 --> 00:57:30,847
If it happens like my dream...

914
00:57:31,200 --> 00:57:33,450
...in five seconds that man will
walk in through the door.

915
00:57:37,090 --> 00:57:43,460
Five, four, three, two, one.

916
00:57:45,434 --> 00:57:46,834
Hello.

917
00:57:57,399 --> 00:57:59,109
What are you doing here?

918
00:57:59,634 --> 00:58:01,602
Wow. It was true.

919
00:58:02,334 --> 00:58:04,047
It's the same as my dream.

920
00:58:05,087 --> 00:58:06,983
I didn't come here to see
you today, Nam Hongjoo.

921
00:58:10,434 --> 00:58:13,657
I came see the two of you
as Park Junmo's attorney.

922
00:58:22,232 --> 00:58:24,501
With this much I believe that
this isn't a coincidence but fate.

923
00:58:25,802 --> 00:58:27,037
You know him, don't you?

924
00:58:30,534 --> 00:58:31,608
I'm curious.

925
00:58:32,242 --> 00:58:34,344
The trivial decision I changed...

926
00:58:35,767 --> 00:58:37,047
...will that one decision stop...

927
00:58:38,015 --> 00:58:40,383
...the horrible moment
that will take place...

928
00:58:41,590 --> 00:58:43,053
...very soon?

929
00:59:01,738 --> 00:59:08,502
"The late Jung Ilsong"

930
00:59:23,293 --> 00:59:26,345
"Prosecutor's Room,
Prosecutor Jung Jaechan"

931
00:59:26,430 --> 00:59:28,302
"While You Were Sleeping"

932
00:59:28,387 --> 00:59:29,249
Your Soyun...

933
00:59:29,334 --> 00:59:31,835
You'll lose your
daughter's talent and future.

934
00:59:31,934 --> 00:59:32,835
I'll go see the prosecutor.

935
00:59:32,934 --> 00:59:33,479
Mom.

936
00:59:33,564 --> 00:59:35,204
I'll sob and beg.

937
00:59:35,289 --> 00:59:37,373
Please don't beg.

938
00:59:37,774 --> 00:59:39,083
I couldn't sleep more than five hours...

939
00:59:39,168 --> 00:59:41,124
...for the past four days
because of Park Junmo's case.

940
00:59:41,209 --> 00:59:42,296
I used to be a prosecutor.

941
00:59:42,381 --> 00:59:45,168
Other lawyers can't even open up
their mouths at the prosecutor's office...

942
00:59:45,267 --> 00:59:45,975
...but I'm different.

943
00:59:46,060 --> 00:59:48,241
I never assaulted my wife.

944
00:59:48,934 --> 00:59:49,747
Attorney Lee!

945
00:59:50,005 --> 00:59:52,915
I have someone who
cheers me on like you, Father.

946
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:55,225
Jung Jaechan. All the best.

947
00:59:56,069 --> 00:59:59,747
She's someone who will say that
it's okay whether I achieve it or not.

948
01:00:05,200 --> 01:00:14,101
"While You Were Sleeping"
